    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I just finished baking these.  Awesome cookies.  Thanks for the recipe ðŸ™‚ </>Happy Holidays!</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-12196" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/07455026458904632093" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">chris</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/12/for-that-very-reason/#comment-12196"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-12-23T23:54:00-05:00">Tuesday, December 23, 2008 at 11:54 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>These are really incredible cookies and yet they are so simple.  I wondered about the salt as well, but I didn&#8217;t miss it. I noticed that they bake up better and look better if you make them smaller.  I put them in standard-size cupcake papers and then in a tin to give away, so that they won&#8217;t break because they really are a delicate cookie.</></>Also, I made the brown sugar candy.  Needless to say, it was very popular, although I about broke my arm trying to get the caramel to melt into the cream (when I added them together, the caramel got hard as a rock).  All worth it though.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-12197" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/12089397499074523719" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Minti</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/12/for-that-very-reason/#comment-12197"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-03-02T18:21:00-05:00">Monday, March 2, 2009 at 6:21 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
